   &quot;Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Denmark&quot;
   &quot;Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Finland&quot;
   &quot;Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Norway&quot;
   &quot;Forward Deployed Software Engineer: Stockholm&quot;</code></pre>

this is really really really bad reporting on the level of Glenn Beck&#x27;s chalkboard ramblings. And it&#x27;s all okay, because we&#x27;re &quot;just asking questions&quot;<p>&quot;Can we say for sure that Palantir&#x27;s product, Prism, is the big data engine behind the NSA&#x27;s secret tool PRISM?
No, we cannot. A call into Palantir has not been returned. As secretive as Palantir is, we doubt anyone we could reach would confirm much for us, anyway.
But it would certainly be a coincidence if there were a big data NSA program was named PRISM and a Palantir product was named Prism and they were not the same.&quot;
